For developers contributing to the ant tasks:

Please make sure, that you do not reference any classes from FindBugs project directly,
which may lead to run-time dependency to the findbugs.jar.

Current state is, that all the FB ant tasks (except the UnionBugs) can run with only
findbugs-ant.jar being on the ant classpath. Hovewer, because UnionBugs has a runtime
dependency to the UnionResults, it requires additionally findbugs.jar being on the ant classpath.

The current dependencies to FindBugs are:

edu.umd.cs.findbugs.ExitCodes (compiler just uses some constants and do not add any runtime dependency)
edu.umd.cs.findbugs.FindBugs2 (reflection)
edu.umd.cs.findbugs.PrintingBugReporter (reflection)
edu.umd.cs.findbugs.LaunchAppropriateUI (reflection)
edu.umd.cs.findbugs.workflow.Update (reflection)
edu.umd.cs.findbugs.workflow.Filter (reflection)
edu.umd.cs.findbugs.workflow.MineBugHistory (reflection)
edu.umd.cs.findbugs.workflow.SetBugDatabaseInfo(reflection)
edu.umd.cs.findbugs.workflow.UnionResults (hard reference in the class file)

See:
 http://development.lombardi.com/?p=484
 https://sourceforge.net/tracker/?func=detail&aid=2819461&group_id=96405&atid=614693

